\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sa240\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Running beside Carolyn, Elthas decided that perhaps the cheetah wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t so bad after all. It was efficient, covering great distances without tiring, and it was nice to run in sync.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Before long, they were climbing up the winding pass through the southern mountains. Towards Tanaris, they now knew. Gadgetzan was just on the other side of the mountains, and from there, they would be able to hire gryphons to fly back to Theramore. Or they could explore the desert, Elthas mused. Neither of them had seen a proper desert before. It would be a far cry from their usual preference for lush forests though; he doubted they would stay long.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Eagerly, they crested the pass and paused to take in the desert sprawling before them. Sand dunes rippled in all directions, shimmering in the late morning heat. In the distance to the east, they could make out the shimmer of blue water, the sun sparkling off the waves of the ocean. Across that vast ocean somewhere, Kamery was probably completing some task or another for Shaw and SI:7.}}